The US Mission in Nigeria has commended the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission for arresting Osondu Victor Igwilo, a suspected fraudster.Igwilo, according to a tweet by the US Mission, has been on the wanted list of the Federal Bureau of Investigation FBI for a very long time. The US mission also congratulated the EFCC for partnering with the FBI to arrest Igwilo.The tweet reads: “With Justice as our mutual priority, we congratulate @officialEFCC for partnering with the @FBI & arresting long-time wanted suspect Igwilo for fraud conspiracy, money laundering and aggravated identity theft.”https://twitter.com/USinNigeria/status/1503379052626915337?t=pTINvlZbOqktVJ5s5l7Uvw&s=19A statement released by Wilson Uwujaren, EFCC spokesperson on Monday says its operatives arrested Igwilo, an alleged leader of a criminal network who has been on the wanted list of the Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI) since 2018.The anti-graft agency said Igwilo was apprehended in Lagos on Thursday along with three others; Okafor Nnamdi Chris, Nwodu Uchenna Emmanuel, and John Anazo Achukwu at a studio in the Sangotedo area of Lagos.They are said to be involved in money laundering and identity theft to the tune of $100million.